<subSubSection id="54BD11A7FFC2FFF1A3C2F9FDFD1BF921" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC2FFF1A3C2F9FDFD1BF921" blockId="2.[151,1437,1713,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC2FFF1A3C2F9FDFEFBF905" bold="true" box="[151,273,1713,1738]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male: Only Neotropical species of 
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC2FFF1A190F9FDFBE3F906" box="[709,1033,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
<taxonomicName id="DBA739AFFFC2FFF1A190F9FDFCB6F906" box="[709,860,1713,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brachypogon</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="DBA739AFFFC2FFF1A024F9FDFBE3F906" box="[881,1033,1713,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brachypogon</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) with the paramere bearing three subapical, stout, sclerotized spines. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="54BD11A7FFC2FFF0A392F9B5FB09FC4C" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" type="description">
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC2FFF1A392F9B5FBF4F86E" blockId="2.[151,1437,1713,2026]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC2FFF1A392F9B5FEB3F8DD" bold="true" box="[199,345,1785,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">Description.</emphasis>
Male. Head (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC2FFF1A2A3F9B5FDDCF8DE" box="[502,566,1785,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[221,1327,209,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[200,1364,195,1909]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. Head. Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A. Head, eyes separation, frontal view. B. Palpus, lateral view. C. Wing. Scale bar: A = 0.05, B = 0.04 mm, C = 0.16 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257267/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
Fig. 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A179F9B5FDDCF8DE" box="[556,566,1785,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A) dark brown. Eyes with numerous interfacetal spicules, broadly separated medially. Antennal flagellum with dense plume, brown; flagellomere 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A092F852FC3FF8F9" box="[967,981,1822,1846]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="1.0">1</number>
with three apical sensilla coeloconica; flagellomeres 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A26FF80DFE9BF896" box="[314,369,1857,1881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="6.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="2.0">2–11</number>
indistinctly separated; flagellomeres 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A071F80DFC83F896" box="[804,873,1857,1881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13</number>
longer than preceeding flagellomeres; AR 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A631F80DFA72F895" box="[1380,1432,1857,1882]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="0.75">0.75</number>
. Palpus (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC2FFF1A3A1F829FEDDF8B1" box="[244,311,1893,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[221,1327,209,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[200,1364,195,1909]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. Head. Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A. Head, eyes separation, frontal view. B. Palpus, lateral view. C. Wing. Scale bar: A = 0.05, B = 0.04 mm, C = 0.16 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257267/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
Fig. 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A279F82AFEDDF8B1" box="[300,311,1894,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B) pale brown; third segment slender, shorter than 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A0C5F829FC75F8B1" box="[912,927,1893,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A0E4F829FC55F8B1" box="[945,959,1893,1918]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="5.0">5</number>
, with broad, deep, subapical sensory pit; palpal ratio 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A248F8C5FEA4F86E" box="[285,334,1929,1953]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="2.7">2.70</number>
. Mouthparts small, clypeus with two subbasal, two apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC2FFF0A392F8E1FE73FF1A" blockId="2.[151,1437,1713,2026]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,1115]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="480" pageId="2" pageNumber="479">
Thorax. Uniformly dark brown. Scutum sparsely covered with minute setae. Scutellum with four setae, two mesal, two lateral; katepisternum with one slender seta. Legs entirely dark brown; hind tibial comb with 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC2FFF1A66CF89DFAADF826" box="[1337,1351,2001,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="479" value="8.0">8</number>
spines, two short spurs. Foreleg 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A2EEFFD4FE35FF60" box="[443,479,152,175]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">TR</collectingCountry>
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A2BFFFDBFDF7FF7F" box="[490,541,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.75">1.75</number>
, midleg 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A1D0FFD4FD43FF60" box="[645,681,152,175]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">TR</collectingCountry>
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A1E1FFDBFD02FF7F" box="[692,744,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.96">1.96</number>
, hindleg 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A000FFD4FC93FF60" box="[853,889,152,175]" name="Chile" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">TR</collectingCountry>
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A0D1FFDBFC52FF7F" box="[900,952,151,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.75">1.75</number>
; tarsomeres 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A71EFFD4FBB3FF7F" box="[1099,1113,152,176]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="4.0">4</number>
subcylindrical; tarsal claws small, equal in all legs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC3FFF0A392FF93FC28FEA8" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC3FFF0A241FF93FEB9FF37" box="[276,339,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[221,1327,209,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[200,1364,195,1909]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male. Head. Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A. Head, eyes separation, frontal view. B. Palpus, lateral view. C. Wing. Scale bar: A = 0.05, B = 0.04 mm, C = 0.16 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257267/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Fig. 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A21CFFACFEB9FF37" box="[329,339,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C) length 
<quantity id="DB5FEFC9FFC3FFF0A29CFF93FDDAFF38" box="[457,560,223,248]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" unit="mm" value="0.85">0.85 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity id="DB5FEFC9FFC3FFF0A1D1FFACFD01FF38" box="[644,747,224,248]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" unit="mm" value="0.34">0.34 mm</quantity>
, CR 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A071FFACFCB3FF37" box="[804,857,224,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="0.47">0.47</number>
. Membrane hyaline, without marginal macrotrichia in r 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A395FE48FF24FED3" box="[192,206,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="3.0">3</number>
, stigma and anterior veins pale brown; radial cells obsolete; costa with 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A0AFFE48FBE2FED3" box="[1018,1032,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
basal setae and row of 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A640FE48FADBFED3" box="[1301,1329,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="12.0">12</number>
marginal setae, radius with 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A23EFE64FE93FE8F" box="[363,377,296,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.0">1</number>
seta immediately distal to basal arculus, and 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A0C4FE64FC75FE8F" box="[913,927,296,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.0">1</number>
at tip of stigma; r-m crossvein oblique; M 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A6C1FE7AFA76FE8B" box="[1428,1436,310,324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
absent; veins M 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A21BFE03FEB2FEA8" box="[334,344,335,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.0">1</number>
, CuA 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A2F5FE03FE43FEA8" box="[416,425,335,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.0">1</number>
, CuA 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A2BEFE03FE12FEA8" box="[491,504,335,359]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
obsolete at wing margin. Halter whitish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC3FFF0A392FE3EFC6FFD64" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Abdomen. Dark brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC3FFF0A11AFE3EFD7FFE44" box="[591,661,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1353,1375]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,203,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1332]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia, Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A, B (ventral view); C (lateral view); D, E, paramere (ventral view), F, aedeagus (ventral view). Scale bar: A = 0.1 mm, B = 0.064 mm, C = 0.05 mm, D = 0.025 mm, E, F = 0.04 mm. Legends: apex of aedeagus (ap aed), basal apodeme (ba apo), gonostylus (gonost), paramere (pm), spines of paramere (sp pm), sternite 9 (st 9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257268/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Fig. 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A1D1FE3FFD7FFE44" box="[644,661,371,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
): Tergite 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A054FE3FFCE5FE44" box="[769,783,371,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="9.0">9</number>
broad, tapering gradually, apex truncated, proctiger large, quadrate, weakly sclerotized, with anterior margin notched; sternite 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A0C9FEDBFC40FE60" box="[924,938,407,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="9.0">9</number>
narrow, rectangular, about 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A7B4FEDAFB05FE60" box="[1249,1263,406,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="5.0">5</number>
times as broad as long, posterior margin transverse. Gonocoxite moderately long, stout, 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A086FEF7FC1FFE1C" box="[979,1013,443,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1.8">1.8</number>
X longer than width, narrowed at 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A62DFEF7FA6EFE1C" box="[1400,1412,443,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A6DBFEF7FA76FE1C" box="[1422,1436,443,467]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="4.0">4</number>
of total length; gonostylus slender, 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A170FE92FDBCFE38" box="[549,598,478,503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="0.62">0.62</number>
as long as gonocoxite, slightly curved, tip pointed. Paramere (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC3FFF0A64DFE92FAB5FE38" box="[1304,1375,478,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1353,1375]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,203,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1332]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia, Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A, B (ventral view); C (lateral view); D, E, paramere (ventral view), F, aedeagus (ventral view). Scale bar: A = 0.1 mm, B = 0.064 mm, C = 0.05 mm, D = 0.025 mm, E, F = 0.04 mm. Legends: apex of aedeagus (ap aed), basal apodeme (ba apo), gonostylus (gonost), paramere (pm), spines of paramere (sp pm), sternite 9 (st 9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257268/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Figs 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A607FE93FAB5FE38" box="[1362,1375,479,503]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E) triangular, sclerotized, anterior margin broad, U-shaped, tapering, with three subapical, stout, sclerotized spines, apex pointed extending to level of posterior margin of segment 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A020FD6BFC7EFDF0" box="[885,916,551,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="10.0">10</number>
. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="849C5EA9FFC3FFF0A777FD6AFB8DFDF0" box="[1058,1127,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1353,1375]" captionTargetBox="[159,1425,203,1326]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,193,1332]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male genitalia, Brachypogon (Brachypogon) ginue n. sp. A, B (ventral view); C (lateral view); D, E, paramere (ventral view), F, aedeagus (ventral view). Scale bar: A = 0.1 mm, B = 0.064 mm, C = 0.05 mm, D = 0.025 mm, E, F = 0.04 mm. Legends: apex of aedeagus (ap aed), basal apodeme (ba apo), gonostylus (gonost), paramere (pm), spines of paramere (sp pm), sternite 9 (st 9)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/257268/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
Fig. 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A70DFD6BFB8DFDF0" box="[1112,1127,551,575]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A,B, F) hyaline, triangular, basal apodeme abruptly bent ventrally, lateral arms slightly curved, heavily sclerotized to the level of basal arch, basal arch nearly straight, extending to 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A136FD23FD6CFD48" box="[611,646,623,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="0.4">0.4</number>
of total length, distal portion stout, triangular, produced beyond the distal level of gonocoxites by a short distance, narrow apex folded.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC3FFF0A392FDFAFE74FD00" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1115]" box="[199,414,694,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1C18422CFFC3FFF0A392FD96FB09FC4C" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1115]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC3FFF0A392FD96FE38FD3C" bold="true" box="[199,466,730,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Taxonomic discussion.</emphasis>
This new species belongs to the 
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC3FFF0A011FD97FC6DFD3D" box="[836,903,731,754]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">impar</emphasis>
group, typically with unadorned wing and vein M 
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A3E5FDB3FF57FCD8" box="[176,189,767,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="2.0">2</number>
absent. This new species keys out to couplet 
<quantity id="DB5FEFC9FFC3FFF0A185FDB3FCE1FCD8" box="[720,779,766,791]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.096" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" unit="in" value="24.0">24 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="78363FDDFFC3FFF0A041FDB2FBD7FCD8" author="Spinelli" box="[788,1085,766,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" refString="Spinelli, G. R. &amp; Grogan, W. L. Jr. (1998) A revision of the Neotropical predaceous midges of Brachypogon (Brachypogon) Kieffer (Diptera: Ceratopogonidae). Insecta Mundi, 12 (1 - 2), 59 - 79." type="journal article" year="1998">
Spinelli &amp; Grogan (
<number id="AA6F500BFFC3FFF0A0ACFDB3FBDFFCD8" box="[1017,1077,767,791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, where 
<taxonomicName id="DBA739AFFFC3FFF0A7CCFC4CFF01FCF4" authority="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC3FFF0A7CCFC4CFAF6FCD8" box="[1177,1308,767,791]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">B. insularis</emphasis>
Spinelli &amp; Grogan
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A26EFC6EFE9CFCF4" box="[315,374,802,827]" name="Cuba" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DBA739AFFFC3FFF0A2EDFC6FFCBDFCF4" authority="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" box="[440,855,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Brachypogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="480" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ecuadorensis">
<emphasis id="2ED39E3EFFC3FFF0A2EDFC6FFD85FCF4" box="[440,623,803,827]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">B. ecuadorensis</emphasis>
Spinelli &amp; Grogan
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A0F2FC6EFC04FCF4" box="[935,1006,802,827]" name="Belize" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Belize</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A748FC6EFB90FCF4" box="[1053,1146,802,827]" name="Ecuador" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and northern 
<collectingCountry id="64B002BCFFC3FFF0A67CFC6EFA87FCF4" box="[1321,1389,802,827]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="480">Brazil</collectingCountry>
are recognized. However, in these two species the gonocoxite is not narrowed at ¾ of its total length, the aedeagus exhibits conspicuous longitudinal wrinkles and the paramere lack the subapical sclerotized spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
